]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"3dec97",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"Diagnosis is clinical, and other possible causes must be ruled out, including infection, malignancy, vasculitis, and drug reaction. Serum ferritin levels >2500 ng/mL are highly specific for this condition and reflect disease activity."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
