"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"c27857",
"children":[
"Treatment is based on disease severity. ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs",
"children":[
"NSAIDs"
]
},
" are generally used as first-line agents in management of mild disease; glucocorticoids are useful in patients with more severe disease. Life-threatening disease is treated with glucocorticoids and an interleukin-1 receptor antagonist, such as anakinra or canakinumab."
]
}
]
